import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Group by origin and destination airports and sum the counts
    grouped_data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().reset_index()
    
    # Calculate the total number of flights for each airport
    airport_counts = grouped_data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    # Get the top 10 busiest airports
    top_10_airports = airport_counts.head(10)
    
    # Plot the bar chart
    ax = top_10_airports.plot(kind='bar')
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels if necessary
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    
    # Set a max of 20 ticks on x-axis
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What are the top 10 busiest airports in terms of number of flights?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of number of flights between airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    G = nx.from_pandas_edgelist(data, source='origin', target='destination', edge_attr='count', create_using=nx.DiGraph())
    
    pos = nx.spring_layout(G)
    nx.draw(G, pos, with_labels=True, node_size=1000, node_color='skyblue', font_size=10, font_weight='bold')
    edge_labels = nx.get_edge_attributes(G, 'count')
    nx.draw_networkx_edge_labels(G, pos, edge_labels=edge_labels, font_size=8)
    
    plt.title('What are the most popular routes in terms of number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['count'])
    plt.xticks([1], ['Count'])
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    avg_count = data['count'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_count, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_count:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights between airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from geopy.distance import great_circle

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    def calculate_distance(origin, destination):
        return great_circle(origin, destination).miles

    data['distance'] = data.apply(lambda row: calculate_distance(row['origin'], row['destination']), axis=1)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['count'], data['distance'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Distance Between Airports (miles)')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of flights and the distance between airports?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
